# Product Business Modeling Rule

Business Modeling is Agent-neutral Core. Cursor rules are runtime guidance only.

- Read `docs/product/BUSINESS_MODEL_OVERVIEW.md` first when present.
- Use canonical Work Item files and the frozen State Schema.
- Keep dictionary, index, schema, objects, relationships, actions, states and rules aligned by stable IDs.
- Keep business attributes separate from data fields.
- Keep each lifecycle bound to one business object and context-dependent values out of intrinsic attributes.
- Use `BMD-xxx` for D2 / D3 decisions.
- After every persistent Core write: consistency report → overview refresh → requested downstream views.
- At normal completion, show only the overview.
- Do not directly edit `docs/design/**` from Business Modeling and do not seal without human approval.
